        "cde_spedps",
        "ca_dashboard"
      ],
      "value": "With only 15 autistic students reported district-wide, the 100% general-education inclusion rate reflects a very small enrollment \u2014 a single placement change can shift the percentage substantially, so this number should be interpreted with caution. Academic outcomes are below standard across all measured groups: all students are 47 points below in English and 85 points below in math, and Students with Disabilities (a broader group that includes autism but is not autism-specific) sit 132 points below standard in English and 182 points below in math. Chronic absenteeism is 25% for SWD versus 24% overall, and SWD suspensions (3%) are similar to the all-students rate (4%). These numbers reflect the 2024-25 school year for academic and attendance data and the prior school year for special-education placement."
